claim.claim-text:
1. A computerized method performed by a first distribution device for distribution of digital content to a user device, the first distribution device selected from one or a plurality of distribution devices, at least the first distribution device communicatively coupled to a location partner, the computerized method comprising:
receiving user identification data and a request for digital content, the user identification data identifying the user device;
verifying the user identification data;
transmitting the user identification data, and payment information associated with the requested digital content to the location partner;
determining whether the requested digital content contains subject matter that is allowed for the user device with the user identification data;
receiving authorization data from the location partner to transmit the requested digital content to the user device; and
transmitting the requested digital content to the user device.

21. A computerized method performed by a first distribution device for distribution of digital content to a user device, the first distribution device selected from one or a plurality of distribution devices, at least the first distribution device communicatively coupled to a location partner, the computerized method comprising:
receiving user identification data and a request for digital content, the user identification data identifying the user;
verifying the user identification data;
transmitting the user identification data, and payment information associated with the requested digital content to the location partner;
requesting authorization data from the location partner whether the requested digital content contains subject matter that is allowed for the user device with the user identification data;
receiving authorization data from the location partner to transmit the requested digital content to the user device; and
transmitting the requested digital content to the user device.

22. A computerized method performed by a first distribution device for distribution of digital content to a user device, the first distribution device selected from one or a plurality of distribution devices, at least the first distribution device communicatively coupled to a location partner, the computerized method comprising:
receiving user identification data and a request for digital content, the user identification data identifying the user;
verifying the user identification data;
relaying the user identification data, and payment information associated with the requested digital content to the location partner;
waiting for customization data from the location partner who ascertains that the requested digital content contains subject matter that is allowed for the user with the user identification data;
receiving customization data from the location partner to transmit the requested digital content to the user device; and
transmitting the requested digital content to the user device.
